name: Philippine Forest Turtle
description:
Palawan turtle or Leyte pond turtle, this freshwater turtle is native to the Palawan islands of the Philippines. Because of habitat loss and too much catching by collectors, they have dramatically decreased in numbers.

Its vertebral scutes have a rather gingko shape. It also has a gradation of pale-white to yellowish coloration line to be found near its ears.

In Philippine folklore, "the turtle is accredited with extraordinary sagacity and cunning. It is another example of the type of tale showing the victory of the weak and cunning over the strong but stupid." - Mabel Cook Cole 

Source: https://owlcation.com/stem/The-Top-Ten-Critically-Endangered-Animals-in-the-Philippines
